   834                              <1> prepareDir:
   835                              <1> ;Used to transfer the current directory if it is necessary.
   836                              <1> ;Always necessary if the user specified a subst drive. Else only if 
   837                              <1> ; a relative path is specified.
   838                              <1> ;Input: al = 1-based drive letter
   839                              <1> ;Output: rdi = Pointing at where to place chars from source string
   840                              <1> ;        rbx -> Pointing at the point before which chars cannot be placed
   841                              <1> ;   If CF=CY => Drive invalid or drive letter too great
   842 00001842 56                  <1>     push rsi    ;Push ptr to source string
   843 00001843 E8A4640000          <1>     call dosCrit1Enter ;CDS/DPB cannot be touched whilst we read the pathstring
