  1840                              <1> ;       If creating, delChar must be set to 0E5h. Not needed for opening!
  1841                              <1> ;       This is set by default by the entry to Disk ops routine into DOS.
  1842                              <1> ;
  1843                              <1> ;Output: If CF=NC: - CurrentSFT filled in except for wNumHandles and bFileAttrib
  1844                              <1> ;                  - wDeviceInfo is set except for inherit bit
  1845                              <1> ;        If CF=CY: - Return fail
  1846                              <1> ;
  1847                              <1> ;
  1848                              <1> ;Check if file exists. If it does, build SFT and truncate if not char dev. 
  1849                              <1> ;   If not, create disk entry.
  1850                              <1> ;Check if the device was a char device by checking curDirCopy.
  1851                              <1> ;If disk, get dpb. We check if the parent dir was found.
  1852                              <1> 
  1853                              <1> ;First set the additional open mode bits, time and date, ownerPSP and 
  1854                              <1> ; file pointer to start of file fields of the SFT
